                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18201</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Representative <persName type="from"
                            >Rodgers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-19T21:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 19, 1916, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. In reply to Department’s 85, May 18. Obregon says troops have moved north
                    only to comply promises for the protection of border. Asserts no trouble in all
                    probability.</p>
                <p>Obregon denied truth report current to-day that he is leaving for north very
                    soon. He appears in good humor.</p>
                <p>This statement obtained by trustworthy agent mine. Continuing investigation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rodgers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
